    {
        "content": "<p>The fence private data trait in the dma fence series seems like it should just be <code>RcuFreeSafe</code></p>",
        "id": 599129591,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780312263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The safety requirement probably is quite complicated, given possibility that the contents are accessed after <code>drop_in_place_before_gp</code></p>",
        "id": 599160409,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1780320814
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"519727\">Alice Ryhl</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291566-Library/topic/Consolidate.20.60PollCondVarBox.60.20into.20.60Rcu.2ABox.60/near/599129591\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The fence private data trait in the dma fence series seems like it should just be <code>RcuFreeSafe</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yeah, I had the same feeling when peeking the code. Glad that you took a good look ;)</p>",
        "id": 599163695,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780321599
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"413824\">Gary Guo</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/291566-Library/topic/Consolidate.20.60PollCondVarBox.60.20into.20.60Rcu.2ABox.60/near/599160409\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The safety requirement probably is quite complicated, given possibility that the contents are accessed after <code>drop_in_place_before_gp</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Maybe, but I feel this is the right abstraction, i.e. if a type can \"pre-drop\" itself into a sane state then it'll be good having RCU readers racing with <code>kfree_rcu()</code>.</p>",
        "id": 599164302,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780321752
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Actually, the fence thing is not the same thing as <code>RcuFreeSafe</code></p>",
        "id": 599164393,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780321778
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's perfectly safe to free the memory holding an RcuBox after less than one grace period after calling drop.</p>",
        "id": 599164625,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780321842
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>by \"holding an RcuBox\" you mean holding the pointer or?</p>",
        "id": 599164949,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780321925
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i.e.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">RcuBox</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;..&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>Foo</code> can be freed without waiting for RCU grace period?</p>",
        "id": 599165279,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780322011
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes</p>",
        "id": 599165304,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780322018
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>The point is, you can invalidate Foo by invoking kfree_rcu(), and then it's still valid to read it for one grace period.</p>",
        "id": 599165381,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780322038
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>But only if the reader owns a refcount on the memory (or otherwise keeps the memory alive).</p>",
        "id": 599166103,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1780322202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, I see. So <code>RcuBox</code> is good enough here, we just need to make sure the user use an <code>RcuBox</code> here.</p>",
        "id": 599168625,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780322806
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"sd\">/// The underlying object will stay alive for one RCU grace period,</span>\n<span class=\"sd\">/// so it's safe that an RCU reader exists when `drop()`.</span>\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">trait</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RcuDrop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RcuDrop</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">RcuBox</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">A</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>?</p>",
        "id": 599169232,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1780322955
    }
]